AGI - "I am pleased that, clearly Mario Draghi > is a very authoritative person, we talk about an Italian for a role like this. After that I continue to say a trivial thing, that is, all this debate here is philosophy." The President of the Council, Giorgia Meloni>, said this at a press point at the end of the EU summit. "But that's not how it works. that is, this tendency to try to decide who does what before citizens vote is a tendency on which you will never find me because it works that citizens vote, who decide who has more weight and who has less weight to make their own proposals that determine what are the possible majorities," he added. "And the outcome of this reasoning begins to speak of names. So I am not interested in this debate, I will not participate in this debate," he said.
&nbsp;
The proposal for the common debt > "is supported by the Italian Government", said the premier, "Enrico Letta puts the question that was then resumed in the next debate and in the Council conclusions on the ability to reopen a debate to mobilize private capital on these challenges, so that those capitals can remain in the European market instead of finding, too often, better conditions in other realities".
&nbsp;
"This was the last European Council of this legislature when we meet again we will be in a different scenario. And what I can hope, despite the work we have done in these months in this year and a half in which we have tried to change the priorities or the way of seeing Europe on some great subjects, I think of the issue of migration but not only, I think of the theme of environmental sustainability linked to economic and social sustainability," said Meloni, "insomma, I hope that when we meet next time we will be facing a different Europe, to respond to a Europe more
<h2>"To change Europe what did not work"</h2>
"What I am interested is that both Enrico Letta, from what we have seen today, and Mario Draghi from that from anticipation, from the statements he has made of another relationship that is that on competitiveness, that is two people considered - simplify - Europeanists, in reality they tell us that Europe must be changed and this is a very interesting debate and it is the debate that needs to be done because otherwise who will do something, if one does not do it another. I'd like to know if we want to change what didn't work," Meloni said, "today even those who until yesterday told us that it was okay, that it was all right, today they count with the fact that priorities have to be others. I would like this campaign to take place on these matters." &nbsp;
&nbsp;
Then the case Ilaria Salis>: "I don't know if he's going to run, I don't think he's gonna change anything from the work the government is doing and I think he has to ensure. I have already said that the politicization of this matter in my opinion I do not know how much it helps the resolution of the case itself but then obviously everyone makes the choices he wants to make, and especially those concerning Ilaria Salis in itself I do not allow me to judge them, they will be choices he will have evaluated. And nothing changes.
&nbsp;
To a question about the imminent celebrations of 25 April, Meloni replied: "I was also last year to lay a crown of flowers with the President of the Republic, as I always do for the celebrations of this nation and do it with the utmost respect for my role. What I had to say about fascism I said a hundred times and I don't think I should repeat it again." &nbsp;
<h2>"194 law of extreme equilibrium, we do not want to change it"</h2>
Another hot topic the controversy about abortion: "It seems to me that this is also another fake news, as it was told is then also bounced abroad and all give us lessons. The amendment which was tabled in the decree Pnrr refers exactly to the text of Law 194. Law 194 provides for it," he explained on the participation in the consultants of representatives of pro-life associations. "I think that in reality those who want to change Law 194 are left because we have never proposed to amend Law 194. But when you ask for the application of law 194 also in prevention, because law 194 is a law of extreme balance, a law well made, you tear your clothes. And then you must also have the courage to say things as they are. You want to change law 194, it's not me who wants to change it. The others want to change it, tell us and assume responsibility. But what is being done now is to reiterate the concepts already foreseen in Law 194", he added. "I think we have to guarantee a free choice. I think that in order to ensure a free choice you must have all the information and opportunities of the case. And this is what Law 194 provides and I think it's the right thing to do," he concluded.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
"In recent weeks I have read so many of those falsehoods on my account that I really start to fear that Italy can become the home of fake news. And one of those falsehoods is that I would have given input to such an initiative," said the President of the Council to a question on the hypothesis of the sale of the Agency AGI>, "the official commune that I do not know if those who inspire these readings were accustomed to using the Italian State's participatory to solve the private problems of their friends or perhaps to draw relatives, it is possible that it was so, but it is not my reading. So I don't know what Eni's doing with Agi, whether or not he's going to sell. I have never dealt with this matter and I do not care about this matter because I believe that the State's participations should do above all the interests of the participants, clearly trying to do their best for that part of national interest they have."
&nbsp;
"I do not deal with this matter and frankly, I do not have a comment to make, I do not know if there is a negotiation, what are the terms of the negotiation. I don't have a comment to do, I don't compete and I don't think I have to compete," he said, "then you could ask me: but is it normal that a state participatory that has a government control, hold a press agency? Because it would be a sensible question, but it's always been so, it's not that I bought the Agi or bought it the Eni when I was there to the government. Because maybe someone else could say: Is it normal that a state participant who is controlled by the Italian government has a press agency? Perhaps this could be read by some as possible limitation of freedom of press. Either way, it wouldn't have been for me because I don't take care of the Ag neither of Eni nor of someone else." &nbsp;
<h2>"Par condicio? The Regulation is the same as before.
Also this other great fake news on the par condicio> has entertained me," continued the premier, "that is, it has entertained me that today I want to control the press and I want to limit the par condicio because the regulation remains what was before. So let me know if today I want to check the press because the regulation remains what was before, before they controlled the press in the election campaign and it was ok?" "Every day I read about the objectively surreal reconstructions. Now we want to imprison journalists when the proposal that removes the prison to journalists for disfamation has as first signature Alberto Balboni of Brothers of Italy. Because I tell you that the prison for journalists for defamation is there and there is a law of Brothers of Italy that is taking away the prison for defamation. So it's all a bit surreal," he added.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
"All these stories that bounce abroad that tell about an Italy in which almost there would be some drift I don't think that we do as a whole as a nation a beautiful figure", he concluded, "because when things get hurt, it's normal and it's right that they criticize but that they become inventive in order to criticize them frankly it doesn't seem a good service." &nbsp;
